                <h1>Mona Lisa: Unveiling the Masterpiece's Mysterious Background</h1>
                <p>The Mona Lisa, painted by Leonardo da Vinci in the early 16th century, is one of the most famous artworks in history. The portrait depicts Lisa Gherardini, the wife of a Florentine merchant, and is celebrated for its exquisite detail and the subject's enigmatic expression. It reflects the Renaissance emphasis on humanism and realism.</p>
